claim.claim-text:
1. A method of adapting a golf course for playing golf at night using a glow in the dark golf ball comprising the steps of: 
selecting an elongated flexible light source; 
placing said elongated flexible light source along the perimeter of a golf course putting green; 
anchoring said placed elongated flexible light source to the earth to provide a visible outline marking of the golf course putting green; and 
marking the golf course green golf hole with night visible markings; 
whereby a golfer can play golf in the dark by driving a glow in the dark ball towards the inside of the perimeter lighted golf green and night visible golf green golf hole.
